data.text: MORRISVILLE:David J Robbins, 61, of Morrisville, passed away unexpectedly on Friday, November 20, 2021 at his home.He was born on October 27, 1960 in the Town of Lebanon, a son of the late Emmet and Stella Thorton Robbins and graduated from Hamilton High School.He married Lisa M. Whipple on February 1, 1999 in the Town of Fenner. Lisa predeceased him on October 15, 2015. He later married Brenda L. Karns on June 24, 2017 in Oriskany Falls. David owned and operated TaHellNBac Dairy, Eaton.He enjoyed hunting but farming and his family were his life.Surviving are his wife Brenda; his mother in law Joyce Karns of Arkport; his children and grandchildren, Brittany and Josh Haitian of Madison and children, Jayla, Skylar, Payton and Hunter; Brandi Eaton of Oriskany Falls, children, Jayden, Brayden, Kameron, Gavin and Keagan; Loretta Robbins and Mike Maggio of Deposit; Delia Robbins of Eaton; step children, Jeremy and Laura Barringer of TX; Justin and Amy Barringer of Morrisville, children Jonas, Stella, Michelle, Sidney and Liam; Curtis and Whitney Barringer of Camden, children, Jade, Jewel and Sadie; Chris and Paula Barringer of Fenner; Steven and Nicole Barringer of Taberg; his siblings Leon Robbins, Eva Ferguson, Dawn Roher, Blance Robbins, Tina Hoag, Junior Robbins, Cathy Dato, Louise Seaton, Bill Robbins, Mickey Allen, Alicia Hill and Richard Robbins; many nieces, nephews and cousins. He was predeceased by a brother Paul Robbins.Funeral services will be held Wednesday, November 24, 2021 at 3:00 PM at the Burgess & Tedesco Funeral Home , 31 Cedar St. Morrisville, NY 13408.Interment will be private in Woodlawn Cemetery, Hamilton. Friends are invited to call on Wednesday from Noon to 3:00 PM prior to the service. To sign the book of memories online or leave a condolence go to: burgessandtedescofuneralhomes.com.
